    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Printed cards used in several Christian denominations, either given by a minister or deacon to identify those of proper status in the church to receive the eucharist, or given at the time of a person's first communion, serving as both documentation of the event and as a commemorative token. </Note_Text>
